                    "company": "Delft University of Technology",
                    "description": "Early Stage Researcher in the SuPER-W Program Department of Sanitary Engineering Faculty of Civil Engineering and Geosciences Project: Steering Product Formation in High-Pressure Anaerobic Digestion Systems \n\nThis particular research project aims to explore the feasibility that inside the context of a biobased economy, wastewater can become an innovative source of organic \u201cfeedstocks\u201d. The use of high-pressure technology, which is widely applied in other fields of industrial biotechnology, could reveal interesting features of microbial communities which can be exploited to improve the overall performance and stability of the bioprocess.\n\n\u2022 Performed independent research into high-pressure anaerobic digestion to advance scientific knowledge in resource recovery from wastewater. These valuable contributions are summarized in 4 scientific publications, participation in 5 international academic conferences, 5 Marie Curie training workshops and industrial internship at Paques BV, Netherlands.\n\u2022 Learned new laboratory techniques such as Next Generation Sequencing and Flow Cytometry and applied this expertise in carrying out enhanced experiments under supervision of senior lab members.\n\u2022 Performed accurate quantitative analysis of research data in R and OriginLab software.",
